        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "# GS1 Grader Usage Examples\n",
                "\n",
                "This notebook demonstrates how to use the GS1 Grader API to grade Data Matrix codes."
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": null,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "from gs1grader.grader_api import DataMatrixGradeAPI\n",
                "\n",
                "grader = DataMatrixGradeAPI()\n",
                "\n",
                "image_path = \"./images/datamatrix_2d_original.png\"\n",
                "\n",
                "grade, explanation = grader.grade_datamatrix(image_path=image_path, grade_type=\"modulation\", explanation_path=\"./grade_explanation\")"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": 2,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "image/png": "",
                        "text/plain": [
                            "<Figure size 800x800 with 1 Axes>"
                        ]
                    },
                    "metadata": {},
                    "output_type": "display_data"
                }
            ],
            "source": [
                "# Let's visualize the image we're grading\n",
                "import cv2\n",
                "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
                "\n",
                "# Read the image\n",
                "img = cv2.imread(image_path)\n",
                "\n",
                "# Convert from BGR to RGB (OpenCV uses BGR by default, matplotlib uses RGB)\n",
                "img_rgb = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)\n",
                "\n",
                "# Display the image\n",
                "plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8))\n",
                "plt.imshow(img_rgb)\n",
                "plt.title('Data Matrix Image')\n",
                "plt.axis('off')\n",
                "plt.show()\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": null,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "text/plain": [
                            "'A'"
                        ]
                    },
                    "execution_count": 3,
                    "metadata": {},
                    "output_type": "execute_result"
                }
            ],
            "source": [
                "grade"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": 4,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "image/png": "",
                        "text/plain": [
                            "<Figure size 800x800 with 1 Axes>"
                        ]
                    },
                    "metadata": {},
                    "output_type": "display_data"
                }
            ],
            "source": [
                "exp_img = cv2.imread(f\"{explanation}.png\")\n",
                "\n",
                "exp_img_rgb = cv2.cvtColor(exp_img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)\n",
                "\n",
                "plt.figure(figsize=(8,8))\n",
                "plt.imshow(exp_img_rgb)\n",
                "plt.axis('off')\n",
                "plt.show()"
            ]
        }
    ],
